Section 1:
1 L.D. 324
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
4 STATE OF MAINE
5 SENATE
6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 224,
9 L.D. 324, “An Act to Increase Reading Proficiency in Public Schools”
10 Amend the amendment by striking out the substitute title and replacing it with the
11 following:
12 'An Act Regarding Funding for Educational Programs and Opportunities'
13 Amend the amendment by striking out everything after the substitute title and inserting
14 the following:
15 'Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §253, sub-§10 is enacted to read:
18 10. Funding for educational programs and opportunities. The commissioner may
19 raise and expend private funds to support a fund established for specific educational
20 programs and opportunities.
21 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
22 allocations are made.
23 EDUCATION, DEPARTMENT OF
24 Innovative Teaching and Learning Z394
25 Initiative: Provides ongoing funds for an early literacy grant program as well as for grant
26 programming related to the implementation of best practices for mathematics instruction
27 in schools.
28 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS 2025-26 2026-27
29 All Other $500 $500
30 __________ __________
31 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS TOTAL $500 $500
3228 ' '
33 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
34 section number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR0912(04)
SENATE AMENDMENT
SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 224, L.D. 324
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment changes the title and removes the substantive provisions of
33 Committee Amendment "A." It authorizes the Commissioner of Education to raise and
44 expend private funds to support a fund established for specific educational programs and
55 opportunities.
66 SPONSORED BY: ___________________________________
77 (Senator ROTUNDO, M.)
88 COUNTY: Androscoggin
Page 2 - 132LR0912(04)
SENATE AMENDMENT
